The bid price of a stock should be between .30 and .70 cents. Higher or lower bid prices increases the [[risk|Risk]].

A simple but effective strategy is to [['average-in|Average In]]' as the price of a stock goes down then go [['flat|Flat]]' (selling all shares) when the price goes up to your [[exit price|Exit Price]].